{"author":"lars@oddbit.com","body":"When all encoder layers have identical mappings, the encoder map array is redundant and creates a maintenance burden — every time a keymap layer is added or removed, the encoder map must be updated to match (QMK enforces this with a static assert).\n\n**How to apply:** Replace the `encoder_map` array and `ENCODER_MAP_ENABLE` with an `encoder_update_user()` function:\n\n```c\nbool encoder_update_user(uint8_t index, bool clockwise) {\n    if (index == 0) {\n        tap_code16(clockwise ? KC_BRIU : KC_BRID);\n    } else {\n        tap_code16(clockwise ? KC_VOLU : KC_VOLD);\n    }\n    return false;\n}\n```\n\nIf per-layer encoder behavior is needed later, this approach still works — just switch on `get_highest_layer(layer_state)` inside the function."}